    </header>
    <section class="content">
        <p>Electrical systems are integral to modern vehicles. Key concepts include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Battery:</strong> Supplies electrical power to start the engine and run accessories.</li>
            <li><strong>Alternator:</strong> Charges the battery while the engine runs.</li>
            <li><strong>Fuses and Relays:</strong> Protect electrical circuits from overcurrent and short circuits.</li>
            <li><strong>Multimeter Usage:</strong> Learn to measure voltage, resistance, and continuity.</li>
            <li><strong>Common Electrical Issues:</strong> Dead battery, faulty alternator, bad connections, and blown fuses.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Understanding electrical systems is crucial for diagnosing and repairing many vehicle issues.</p>
